# Build Before Tests

- Before running tests, rebuild the package(s) whose source changed and any direct consumers that load their `dist` outputs.
- For custom-element packages consumed via exports, do not rely on stale `dist`; run the package build first.
- If the exact impacted package set is unclear, default to rebuilding all likely affected packages in the current test path.
- When test failures can be caused by stale artifacts, rebuild first and rerun once before deeper debugging.
